Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

(4 comments)

I'm -1ing just because this is a PoC and it has whitespace damage :)

This looks good as the first part of the patch to expand the schema and start storing the details in the task structures that we need. Personally, I think that this should be distinct from the patch to actually add the new API. We can test this in isolation to ensure that it doesn't change anything from the outside on its own, and make sure that it's internally fully covered. A following patch to *expose* those details through the API will have smaller scope, be easier to validate that we've tested all the API related bits, and make it easy to isolate the change in behavior. We can hold this patch until the next one is ready, but it will be much easier to review them in isolation, as this one is already pretty big.

1st related to database operations
2nd actual changes in tasks operation
3rd new API related changes
